The magnificent Westminster Abbey in London is the perfect place for Kings and Queens to be crowned. Its scale and grandeur is breathtaking and not even pics can do it true justice.

IG has changed a lot and so has my relationship with it. I’m done trying to have a curated page of similar content and theme to please the algo and the masses. I have many great shots of other places outside of NYC and I am going to start sharing my content with no rhyme or reason because at this point I’m fine with the mass unfollowing that is about to come. My gallery is now going to be what pleases me from the pics I take and not what I think will be good clickbait to grow my followers. If you decide to stick around and see content other than NYC then thanks so much for your continued support! Those that stay are the reason I will continue to share on this platform despite the greed grab it has become thanks to the ownership of Meta

I love many genres of photography including street photography. I don’t get much time or opportunity to do street work so I took the opportunity while in Edinburgh to shoot the streets on a rainy night. I love all the small passageways and alleys in the main portion of town and they become even more magical at night either deserted or with people making their way to their destinations. My next few shots will be from my magical night shooting in Edinburgh and I hope you enjoy them as much as I do.

social_posts.post_text:
Ring of Fire - Empty Sky Memorial 

Twice each day (sunrise and sunset) an amazing experience nicknamed the ring of fire occurs at the Empty Sky Memorial in Liberty State Park. It is a testament to the reverence of the architects  that designed this stirring memorial to those that lost their lives due to the attack on the US on Sep 11, 2001. 

While pictures like this one are amazing to see, nothing compares to the experience of being there and seeing the ring materialize to its full burn as captured here.
